Package managerpro.Controller

Class KitchenController

java.lang.Object
managerpro.Controller.KitchenController
public class KitchenController
extends java.lang.Object
A Controller class to control the Kitchen -tab in the JavaFX User interface. Has an intermediary datastorage of Orders and OrderedPortions, based on which the user interface is updated
Author:
OTP7

  • Method Details

    • initialize

      public void initialize()
      Initializer for Kitchen controller. Updates the GUI and adds PropertyChangeListener to Controller.Model to update the Gui whenever changes are made ot database.

    • setPortionDone

      public void setPortionDone​(javafx.scene.input.MouseEvent mouseEvent)
      Event Handler for the "portion ready" Button. Sets the selected ordered portions's status to 1 and if all portions are done, sets the orders status to "readyToServe"
      Parameters:
      mouseEvent - MouseEvent from the button click. Will be changed to ActionEvent at some point

    • orderClicked

      public void orderClicked​(javafx.scene.input.MouseEvent mouseEvent)
      Event Handler for when the user clicks an order on the screen. Sets the selected order to selectedOrder field and finds the first orderedPortion the of selected order and sets it as selectedOrderedPortion
      Parameters:
      mouseEvent - Mouse event from the GUI

    • oPClicked

      public void oPClicked​(javafx.scene.input.MouseEvent mouseEvent)
      Event Handler for when the user clicks an ordered portion. Prints out the ordered portions details to a VBox.
      Parameters:
      mouseEvent - MouseEvent from the gui

    • updateGui

      public void updateGui()
      A Method for updating the JavaFX UI. Clears the children of the HBoxes and VBox, creates a new button for each order, creates button for each orderedPortion of the selected order and prints out the information of the selectedOrderedPortion to the VBox. Wrapped in Platform.runLater() to allow the PropertyChangeListener to call this method on database updates. Neat.

    • tabOpened

      public void tabOpened​(javafx.event.Event event)
      Handles the event of opening the kitchen-tab.
      Parameters:
      event - - The event that is fired when the tab is selected.
